1
00:01:33,480 --> 00:01:34,640
There he is.

2
00:01:34,720 --> 00:01:37,040
That's the cop who bumped into me.
It has to be him.

3
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:40,960
Can't be helped. They're just kids.
If you want to be a con artist,

4
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,200
this comes with the territory.

5
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:45,280
Where will you be traveling today, miss?

6
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:50,200
You've got some nerve,
running off with my money.

7
00:01:50,280 --> 00:01:51,520
Chop off all their legs!

8
00:01:52,440 --> 00:01:54,240
- Stop!
- No!

9
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:55,080
Don't!

10
00:01:56,320 --> 00:01:58,440
There it is. Our money's right there.

11
00:01:58,520 --> 00:02:01,040
But how do we get it?

12
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,440
Let's lure Koh out first.

13
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,800
If only the big guy's left, we can get in.

14
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:17,520
We'll take one honey toast.

15
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:19,800
For drinks, how about…

16
00:02:19,880 --> 00:02:21,120
- Cherry Blossom, dear?
- Yeah.

17
00:02:21,960 --> 00:02:24,520
Cherry Blossom and a White Choc Cocoa.

18
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:27,280
Got it. I'll prepare that for you.

19
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:30,120
But make the honey toast less sweet.

20
00:02:30,200 --> 00:02:31,240
No problem.

21
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,960
And do you have bingsu?

22
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:36,480
Yes, we have chocolate bingsu,

23
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,720
strawberry bingsu, and durian bingsu.

24
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,000
No, that's enough.

25
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,720
Alright, let me confirm your order.

26
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,000
One less-sweet mango honey toast,

27
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:50,480
a Cherry Blossom,
and a White Choc Cocoa. Correct?

28
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,440
No more orders, right?

29
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:58,320
There's only two of us.

30
00:02:58,920 --> 00:03:01,120
Why order so much? Isn't this enough?

31
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,800
Fine, we can go.

32
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,440
I'll take care of it, sir. Calm down.

33
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:07,760
Please sit back, relax, and enjoy the AC.

34
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,840
I'll get your order right out.

35
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:11,240
Alright then, hurry up and make it.

36
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,440
Hey, you're so picky,
ignoring that uncle's muscles.

37
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,680
You're asking for trouble.

38
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:29,120
What choice do I have?
We need to buy time for Angpao.

39
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:36,840
Yes! Great job!

40
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:38,920
My good boy.

41
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:41,280
<i>Pao, how's it going?</i>

42
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:45,280
Don't rush me. It's not easy.

43
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:50,640
I know it's tough,
but hurry up a little, okay?

44
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:04,760
Pao, you need to hurry.

45
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,120
He's starting to catch on.

46
00:04:06,200 --> 00:04:08,520
Order something that'll slow him down.

47
00:04:08,600 --> 00:04:10,880
Something complicated
that takes a while. Got it?

48
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:12,960
Okay, okay.

49
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:20,680
Come on! Three more digits! Three more!

50
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,800
Excuse me.

51
00:04:22,880 --> 00:04:24,200
Yes!

52
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,960
Coming, sir.

53
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:30,840
Aren't you going to serve
some water? I'm thirsty.

54
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,320
Oh, the water.

55
00:04:33,400 --> 00:04:36,320
We serve it with the order.

56
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:39,560
Have you ever been to a decent cafe
to see how service works?

57
00:04:42,680 --> 00:04:44,640
Sir, please be patient.

58
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,840
I'll get the water right away.

59
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:55,560
What are you looking at? Go do it.

60
00:04:57,960 --> 00:04:59,080
Yes!

61
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:23,240
Come on, kid! Hurry up!

62
00:05:23,320 --> 00:05:24,960
Come on. Please.

63
00:05:44,280 --> 00:05:45,320
Here's your water.

64
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:46,760
Go ahead.

65
00:05:50,280 --> 00:05:51,680
Oh no! Sir…

66
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,840
I'm sorry!

67
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,960
- I'm really sorry!
- What the heck are you doing?

68
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:59,520
- I didn't mean to. I just--
- It's all wet.

69
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:00,960
Is there a bathroom?

70
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:03,680
Right over there, in the corner. Go ahead.

71
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:07,360
- Be careful. It's slippery.
- I have work after this.

72
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,080
Angpao, are you done?

73
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,440
Should I just take the safe?

74
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:50,280
Don't eat here anymore. Let's go, dear.

75
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:56,080
Stop acting.

76
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,960
I know…

77
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:05,800
what you two are up to.

78
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:18,840
Excuse me.

79
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,800
Hey!

80
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,960
Did this man hurt you?

81
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:55,280
Your boyfriend hurt you, didn't he?

82
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,840
Yes.

83
00:08:10,040 --> 00:08:12,200
What kind of man are you?

84
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:16,000
Ma'am, should we call the police?

85
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,440
Have him arrested! Let's do it!

86
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:20,800
It's fine.

87
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,080
Hey, wait.

88
00:08:22,160 --> 00:08:24,480
I don't want to make
a big deal out of this.

89
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,200
Wait!

90
00:08:26,280 --> 00:08:27,200
Let's go, dear.

91
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:28,600
- Okay, dear.
- Thank you.

92
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:30,880
But he hurt you!

93
00:08:30,960 --> 00:08:33,480
Hey! How could you love someone like this?

94
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,200
Hey, remember this!

95
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:40,240
Love that hurts each other
like this isn't love.

96
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,600
Two more! Two more digits!

97
00:08:45,680 --> 00:08:47,960
Just two more digits and we're done.

98
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,920
You brat!

99
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:55,000
Where did you hide the money
you stole from us? Tell me now.

100
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,560
The money's there!

101
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,480
- The money's in the safe!
- Tell me!

102
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:01,960
- What?
- The money's in the safe, you fools!

103
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,360
Stubborn, huh?

104
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,400
Take this!

105
00:09:05,160 --> 00:09:07,680
Drag him outside.

106
00:09:07,760 --> 00:09:08,920
Hurry! Give me a hand!

107
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:12,800
The money's in the safe.

108
00:09:12,880 --> 00:09:16,080
Pao? Why aren't you answering, Pao?

109
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,480
Pao!

110
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:22,880
- He's not here.
- Could he have been caught?

111
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,200
I don't think so.

112
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,120
How did Hong and the others get here?

113
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:49,880
No!

114
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,920
- Gotcha!
- Hey!

115
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,200
You do know, right? Tickling

116
00:09:54,280 --> 00:09:56,640
is a brutal form of torture.

117
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,800
Someone can actually have
a heart attack from it.

118
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,560
You're still not going to tell us

119
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:06,960
where you hid the money, huh?

120
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:09,160
Tell us!

121
00:10:09,240 --> 00:10:10,960
Hey! Enough!

122
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:12,960
No! Don't!

123
00:10:13,040 --> 00:10:15,320
I told you already,
the money's in the safe!

124
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,920
Man, you're stubborn.

125
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,080
Are you gonna tell us or not?

126
00:10:23,920 --> 00:10:24,640
Take this!

127
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:25,800
Hey!

128
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:28,760
I just told you.

129
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,880
Why don't you believe me?

130
00:10:32,920 --> 00:10:34,600
Risa! You little brat!

131
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:37,560
<i>Hurry up and get the four million</i>
<i>to ransom your friend right now,</i>

132
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:41,160
<i>or I'll chop up his little worm</i>
<i>and send it to you!</i>

133
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:52,000
Wow, that's super old-school.

134
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,240
What do we do?

135
00:10:56,240 --> 00:10:58,240
No matter what,
we have to save Angpao first.

136
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:24,480
Finally found you, you little brat.

137
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,240
Where's my friend?

138
00:11:38,640 --> 00:11:39,760
Come out.

139
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,960
Hurry up.

140
00:11:43,040 --> 00:11:44,720
Stay right there.

141
00:11:44,800 --> 00:11:47,160
- Help me!
- He's here.

142
00:11:48,360 --> 00:11:52,000
Hope there's no funny business today. Hey!

143
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:56,280
Check that bag.
See if the money's in there. Open it!

144
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,800
Wait.

145
00:12:08,960 --> 00:12:10,240
Let my friend go first.

146
00:12:18,680 --> 00:12:20,240
Don't mess around.

147
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:24,240
Or you'll eat lead.

148
00:12:25,480 --> 00:12:26,760
Stay still.

149
00:12:35,720 --> 00:12:37,560
Slowly.

150
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:39,800
Slowly. Take him!

151
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:42,880
- Take him!
- Let's open it.

152
00:12:42,960 --> 00:12:44,960
Open it… Ta-da!

153
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:47,200
- My money!
- Yes!

154
00:12:47,280 --> 00:12:48,240
Money!

155
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:50,320
We got the money…

156
00:12:50,400 --> 00:12:52,160
Why is there only one sheet?

157
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:01,840
You can't trick us twice. This time,

158
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,920
you're done for!

159
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:07,760
Risa! You little brat!

160
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:13,080
Cut the games and give me my money back!

161
00:13:15,440 --> 00:13:18,040
The money's not with us anymore.

162
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,960
What do you mean by that?

163
00:13:20,040 --> 00:13:22,200
I told you from the start.

164
00:13:22,280 --> 00:13:23,600
Take the tape off first.

165
00:13:27,120 --> 00:13:29,880
I told you already.
Why don't you believe me?

166
00:13:31,320 --> 00:13:34,080
Koh and his friend took all the money.

167
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:37,320
They posed as cops
when they raided your place.

168
00:13:37,400 --> 00:13:38,560
Don't trust them.

169
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:41,360
These kids are cunning as hell, Hong.

170
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:42,720
What?

171
00:13:42,800 --> 00:13:45,200
I was about to open the safe
to get the money,

172
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:47,360
but you two grandpas grabbed me.

173
00:13:47,960 --> 00:13:49,400
Don't you remember?

174
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:50,840
Do you have proof?

175
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:53,240
- Yeah.
- That you saw them take the money?

176
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:54,760
Of course.

177
00:13:58,480 --> 00:13:59,680
Look at this.

178
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:05,120
He swapped the phones
along with the QR code,

179
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,280
so the money got transferred
into his account instead.

180
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:11,880
You guys are evil through and through.

181
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:14,040
Like you're any better.

182
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:17,200
All the money you got
came from scamming people anyway.

183
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:19,000
- Hey!
- Mouthy little brat.

184
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:20,440
- Wait.
- Come on.

185
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:23,320
Let's just figure out what to do next.

186
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:26,520
Figure out what?
I'm getting my money back. That's it.

187
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:30,480
Wait, it's not your money. It's ours.

188
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:32,640
Watch it. I'll smack that mouth of yours.

189
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,000
Want a taste of this?

190
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:36,520
Stop it. No fighting.

191
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,600
There's over five million baht
in that safe.

192
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:43,400
Let 's split it fairly,
half and half. Deal?

193
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,880
If you want our help.

194
00:14:44,960 --> 00:14:46,040
Hey!

195
00:14:46,120 --> 00:14:48,120
Why should I share it with you?

196
00:14:49,080 --> 00:14:50,320
Don't forget, sis.

197
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:52,440
Part of all that money you made

198
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,480
came from me.

199
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:59,040
Even without you,
I could've gotten it myself.

200
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,720
Suit yourself.

201
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:06,360
Whoever gets it, gets it. Your call.

202
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:18,040
<i>To me, it's like a discipline</i>

203
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:20,560
<i>combining psychology,</i>

204
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:23,200
<i>philosophy, investigation,</i>

205
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:26,000
<i>and even science.</i>

206
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:29,840
<i>But it's presented</i>
<i>from a different perspective.</i>

207
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:37,640
<i>We know magic isn't real sorcery.</i>

208
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:42,920
<i>Yet it still captivates people.</i>

209
00:15:44,400 --> 00:15:47,400
<i>It makes them fall for the illusion,</i>

210
00:15:47,480 --> 00:15:50,320
<i>even though it isn't real.</i>

211
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:54,360
KIAT SAMKOR BOXING CAMP

212
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:55,720
<i>Deception</i>

213
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:58,360
<i>isn't that different from magic.</i>

214
00:15:58,440 --> 00:16:00,800
<i>Sometimes, we're the ones performing it.</i>

215
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:07,920
<i>And often, we're just the audience.</i>

216
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,240
No!

217
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:13,840
<i>But one undeniable truth is…</i>

218
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:16,760
<i>we all</i>

219
00:16:17,760 --> 00:16:19,480
<i>enjoy it in some way.</i>

220
00:16:20,040 --> 00:16:22,000
CHILD ADOPTION AGREEMENT

221
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:22,960
No!

222
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:25,720
- Don't!
- Mom!

223
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,880
If you want to blame someone,
blame your mother.

224
00:16:32,960 --> 00:16:35,280
She sent you here to work off her debt.

225
00:17:09,599 --> 00:17:12,760
From the GPS, Koh won't
be coming back anytime soon.

226
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:14,599
The real problem is that big guy.

227
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:16,839
He probably realized
we snuck in yesterday.

228
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,560
He 's watching the shop.
Going in is risky.

229
00:17:18,640 --> 00:17:20,920
Then what do we do now?

230
00:17:21,000 --> 00:17:23,040
Easy. We go in,

231
00:17:23,720 --> 00:17:25,480
pour gasoline everywhere,
and burn it down.

232
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:28,640
Once it's burning, we grab the money.

233
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:32,120
Won't our money burn too, grandpa?

234
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,640
Yesterday, I was this close.

235
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:36,440
Just two more digits,
and I would've cracked the safe,

236
00:17:36,520 --> 00:17:38,240
if you guys hadn't interfered.

237
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:39,680
Or are you just inexperienced?

238
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:40,920
- You amateur!
- Hey, take cover!

239
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,200
The big guy's out of the base.

240
00:17:51,680 --> 00:17:54,160
He's outside now.

241
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:57,280
What are you waiting for?
Split up and follow the plan.

242
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,600
- Quick!
- Let's go!

243
00:17:58,680 --> 00:17:59,520
- Yak, come on!
- Hey.

244
00:18:12,040 --> 00:18:12,920
Confused, huh?

245
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,760
- Can we go in?
- Go ahead.

246
00:18:15,840 --> 00:18:16,800
Fatty!

247
00:18:20,920 --> 00:18:23,160
Good thing all my gear's still here.

248
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:24,760
Looks like they didn't touch the safe.

249
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,480
Hey, come here.

250
00:18:28,400 --> 00:18:30,400
Stash your tools and sit down.

251
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:33,040
Come watch how the pros do it.

252
00:18:33,120 --> 00:18:35,440
Yeah. Let's see.

253
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:38,080
What you're looking at here
isn't something you put on your cheeks.

254
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:47,800
Last time,

255
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,800
what numbers did you get?

256
00:18:49,880 --> 00:18:52,440
1344. Still missing two digits, grandpa.

257
00:18:53,880 --> 00:18:56,960
The missing two could be 66, 77,

258
00:18:57,040 --> 00:18:58,760
or 76… maybe 67.

259
00:18:58,840 --> 00:18:59,760
What?

260
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:03,000
134466.

261
00:19:03,960 --> 00:19:07,080
Error. Just kidding.
Now let 's do this for real.

262
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:10,840
134467.

263
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:14,280
Open. Got it!

264
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:21,680
Where's the money?

265
00:19:28,520 --> 00:19:29,880
You're dead!

266
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,360
Take this!

267
00:19:36,440 --> 00:19:37,960
Help!

268
00:19:38,680 --> 00:19:40,920
Why are you screaming? Run!

269
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,600
Double punch! Backfist!

270
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,880
Look over there!

271
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:54,160
So damn strong.

272
00:19:56,240 --> 00:19:58,840
- Quick, run!
- He's coming!

273
00:19:58,920 --> 00:20:01,440
- Phayak, unlock the car!
- He's coming!

274
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:02,360
Hurry!

275
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,440
Start it, quick!

276
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,400
- Go, grandpa!
- Hurry, Yak!

277
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,680
I said start it!

278
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:12,120
I 'm trying, but it won't start!

279
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,360
You thief!

280
00:20:14,240 --> 00:20:16,960
Grandpa! He's coming!

281
00:20:17,040 --> 00:20:18,120
Grandpa!

282
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,120
Thief! You're dead!

283
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,760
Hurry up!

284
00:20:22,680 --> 00:20:23,400
He's here!

285
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:25,160
- He's here, grandpa!
- He's here!

286
00:20:26,440 --> 00:20:29,280
Good thing the door's locked.

287
00:20:43,440 --> 00:20:45,120
- Hurry up!
- Go!

288
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:48,360
Move!

289
00:20:49,360 --> 00:20:50,480
Go!

290
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,000
Quick!

291
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:56,680
NO MONEY IN THE SAFE, RIS

292
00:20:57,480 --> 00:21:00,680
They know we broke into the safe.
They moved the money.

293
00:21:01,760 --> 00:21:03,760
I knew that guy wasn't ordinary.

294
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:07,560
Then how are we supposed
to get the money back?

295
00:21:08,920 --> 00:21:11,240
Everyone has a weak point.

296
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,200
We'll spot his car
at the next intersection.

297
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,920
Which one?

298
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:27,760
Is that the car?

299
00:21:27,840 --> 00:21:33,120
STOP

300
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,040
A nursing home?

301
00:21:39,120 --> 00:21:41,040
How do you know his car's there?

302
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,760
I put a GPS tracker on it.

303
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,400
What's a GPS?

304
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:49,640
I'll explain later, sis.

305
00:21:52,840 --> 00:21:55,040
Wait, I'm about to win!

306
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:58,080
- I've got incredible luck!
- Calm down.

307
00:21:58,160 --> 00:21:59,640
- Yes!
- The cops are here!

308
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:03,320
Wait for me!

309
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,160
You crazy kid!

310
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,320
Why'd you lie to me?

311
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:12,080
I'm gonna beat you!
You nearly gave me a heart attack!

312
00:22:12,160 --> 00:22:15,040
Who lied to you? I really am a cop.

313
00:22:15,760 --> 00:22:17,040
Aren't you scared?

314
00:22:17,120 --> 00:22:20,240
If you keep this up,
I'll actually lock you up.

315
00:22:21,520 --> 00:22:23,040
Koh, don't be ridiculous.

316
00:22:23,120 --> 00:22:26,360
Like you'd really lock up your own mom.

317
00:22:26,440 --> 00:22:29,520
I'm just having fun,
playing for a little money.

318
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:31,800
But I already lost 500 baht today.

319
00:22:34,160 --> 00:22:35,040
Cheeky, aren't you?

320
00:22:36,160 --> 00:22:38,280
Here, I brought gifts for everyone.

321
00:22:38,360 --> 00:22:39,600
Here you go.

322
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:42,240
This one's for Aunt Dang.

323
00:22:42,320 --> 00:22:44,560
This one's for Aunt Poo.

324
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:46,480
- Thank you!
- There you go.

325
00:22:46,560 --> 00:22:47,560
This one,

326
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:49,720
- Aunt Noi.
- Thanks, dear!

327
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,680
My pleasure.

328
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:52,560
There's one for you too.

329
00:22:53,840 --> 00:22:55,760
Here it is.

330
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,360
Look at this blouse.

331
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:00,560
- Wow, beautiful.
- Isn't it pretty?

332
00:23:00,640 --> 00:23:02,600
- Thank you so much, dear.
- You like it?

333
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:06,160
But this one's special.
It's just for you, Mom. Here.

334
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:14,320
Koh, why did you buy this?

335
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:15,520
This must've cost a fortune.

336
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,000
Come on, Mom. I already bought it.

337
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:21,240
I wanted you to have
something nice to wear. Come here.

338
00:23:21,320 --> 00:23:22,640
I'll help you put it on, okay?

339
00:23:22,720 --> 00:23:25,920
What do I have to do
to have a son like this?

340
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:28,120
Rich, and devoted to his mom.

341
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,680
Such a wonderful son!

342
00:23:30,760 --> 00:23:32,120
Exactly.

343
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:34,160
I like it. It's from you.

344
00:23:35,800 --> 00:23:37,040
It's nothing special.

345
00:23:39,320 --> 00:23:40,480
This young man…

346
00:23:40,560 --> 00:23:43,480
He's not even half as rich as my son!

347
00:23:45,160 --> 00:23:48,520
I know I'm not as rich as your son.

348
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,160
I just wanted to do something nice

349
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:54,000
for the moms. Would you like one?

350
00:23:55,440 --> 00:23:58,440
Take a look first. You might like it.

351
00:23:59,000 --> 00:24:00,720
Here.

352
00:24:00,800 --> 00:24:04,080
This one has a floral pattern. Want it?

353
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,440
Do you want it?

354
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:09,720
I don't want this shirt.

355
00:24:09,800 --> 00:24:12,040
This kind of shirt… My son's name…

356
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:15,000
What was it? Whatever.

357
00:24:15,080 --> 00:24:16,920
He's bought me so many things already.

358
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:18,680
You know what?

359
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,920
He's transferred millions

360
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:22,840
into my bank account.

361
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:27,680
But how come I never see your son

362
00:24:27,760 --> 00:24:31,480
taking care of you? Is he not really rich?

363
00:24:32,880 --> 00:24:34,080
Don't talk about my son!

364
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:38,320
If you don't believe me, I'll show you
my bank account on my phone. Here!

365
00:24:39,840 --> 00:24:42,720
Where's my phone? Who took it?

366
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:44,000
- I was…
- It's in your hand.

367
00:24:44,080 --> 00:24:45,840
Hand? Whose hand?

368
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,840
- Let me see!
- It's not here.

369
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:49,120
Koh!

370
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,920
Why are you teasing her?

371
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:53,120
You know she has Alzheimer's.

372
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,240
- Just a little, Mom.
- You took it?

373
00:24:59,640 --> 00:25:01,200
He really does love his mom.

374
00:25:03,400 --> 00:25:04,800
There it is. His weak spot.

375
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:06,360
If he loves his mom that much,

376
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:09,160
we'll just kidnap her.

377
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,760
Then make him pay ransom to get her back.

378
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:15,920
Sorry.

379
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,520
Scroll down. Yeah, all the way.

380
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:23,200
- It's still not very clear.
- Can you zoom in?

381
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,520
- Zoom.
- Yeah.

382
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:26,680
Just focus on the one
wearing the pearl necklace.

383
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:29,000
Hong, you're really sharp.

384
00:25:29,080 --> 00:25:30,120
And beautiful too.

385
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:35,720
Chirp, chirp.

386
00:25:36,760 --> 00:25:38,280
Ribbit.

387
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:50,600
- Which one is it?
- Which one?

388
00:25:52,040 --> 00:25:52,960
Hurry.

389
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:56,000
- Brake!
<i>- Hey, I checked.</i>

390
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:58,360
His mom's room is 228.

391
00:25:58,440 --> 00:25:59,520
- Gao!
- What?

392
00:25:59,600 --> 00:26:00,800
- Do it.
- This room?

393
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:06,720
Calm down.

394
00:26:23,080 --> 00:26:23,920
Hey, Gao!

395
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:25,720
Found her!

396
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:26,720
Are you sure, grandpa?

397
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:30,600
Hong said the one wearing
the pearl necklace, right, Gao?

398
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:37,960
- Yeah.
- Then that's her.

399
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:41,840
Gao, give her the sedative!

400
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:42,760
Stay still!

401
00:26:42,840 --> 00:26:45,200
Here.

402
00:26:47,040 --> 00:26:49,480
Everyone, we've got the target.

403
00:26:49,560 --> 00:26:52,520
I repeat, we've got the target.
Meet me at the exit.

404
00:26:56,080 --> 00:26:58,240
To the left!

405
00:26:58,880 --> 00:27:00,640
- Right.
- Wait!

406
00:27:02,520 --> 00:27:04,520
At this hour, where are you all going?

407
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:08,840
Well…

408
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,360
There you are!

409
00:27:12,040 --> 00:27:13,440
I've been looking all over for you.

410
00:27:14,240 --> 00:27:15,440
What's going on, Doctor?

411
00:27:15,520 --> 00:27:17,040
Don't ask questions right now.

412
00:27:17,120 --> 00:27:20,480
We need to rush the patient
for a QRTM scan immediately,

413
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:23,200
because there's
severe platelet contraction.

414
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:25,880
After checking with C3PO,

415
00:27:25,960 --> 00:27:29,720
it looks like there's a risk of H5N1.

416
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:34,600
Hurry. If we don't do the QRTM now,

417
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:38,120
the patient could crash at any moment.
And then doing R2D2

418
00:27:38,200 --> 00:27:40,880
could send the patient
into NV Level 2 shock.

419
00:27:41,760 --> 00:27:45,280
Let's go. We'll miss the ride. Hurry.

420
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:47,160
Wait.

421
00:27:48,680 --> 00:27:50,320
Let me see your ID first.

422
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:53,920
ID?

423
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,080
Here's the ID.

424
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:59,800
You wanted the ID, right? The ID is…

425
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:02,200
Is this the one?

426
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:08,480
- That's my ID.
- Is that so?

427
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:10,200
- Where's my ID?
- I might've grabbed the wrong one.

428
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:12,560
Is this the one?

429
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,280
Maybe this one?

430
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:15,520
Or this one?

431
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:17,480
This one?

432
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:18,720
Or this one?

433
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:19,880
This one?

434
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:27,520
Here, take them all.
Figure it out yourself.

435
00:28:27,600 --> 00:28:28,680
Whatever.

436
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,920
<i>Right now, your mom is with me.</i>

437
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:33,920
What?

438
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:38,440
If you want your mom safe,
bring ten million

439
00:28:38,520 --> 00:28:40,160
<i>and trade it for her.</i>

440
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:42,640
Are you crazy?
Who the hell are you people?

441
00:28:42,720 --> 00:28:44,720
<i>No negotiation.</i>

442
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:47,600
Ten million by 3 p.m. tomorrow.

443
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:49,520
Otherwise, your mom dies.

444
00:28:49,600 --> 00:28:51,920
<i>I'll send you the location</i>

445
00:28:52,000 --> 00:28:54,160
<i>for the drop-off.</i>

446
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:55,320
Hello?

447
00:29:05,640 --> 00:29:07,960
<i>Koh, help me!</i>

448
00:29:08,040 --> 00:29:11,600
<i>They took me. They're hurting me.</i>

449
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:13,960
<i>They said they'd kill me</i>

450
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:15,880
<i>if the money doesn't get to them.</i>

451
00:29:15,960 --> 00:29:18,320
<i>Koh, please help me! Hurry!</i>

452
00:29:22,280 --> 00:29:24,200
Yes, one moment.

453
00:29:24,800 --> 00:29:26,560
Mr. Koh, calm down.

454
00:29:28,480 --> 00:29:31,800
I still haven't seen your mother,
honestly.

455
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,760
Are you sure?

456
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:36,080
Yes, but I'll go check--

457
00:29:47,480 --> 00:29:51,160
Koh, want to eat something first?
You'll need your strength.

458
00:29:52,360 --> 00:29:54,440
Mom's been taken. I can't eat.

459
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,080
They still haven't contacted me.

460
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:06,840
If they contact you,
what are you planning to do?

461
00:30:09,360 --> 00:30:12,440
Whatever they want, we do it.
Mom's in their hands.

462
00:30:15,280 --> 00:30:17,040
But half the money here is yours.

463
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,720
I'll pay you back later.

464
00:30:18,800 --> 00:30:21,280
The money doesn't matter.
Your mom's life comes first.

465
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,880
ADD TO CONTACTS
BLOCK NUMBER

466
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:34,200
Quiet!

467
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:36,560
Hey!

468
00:30:36,640 --> 00:30:37,680
Why are you struggling?

469
00:30:38,960 --> 00:30:40,120
Enough already. Stop!

470
00:30:40,200 --> 00:30:42,120
Grandpa! What are you doing?

471
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:44,800
Take the tape off first. Have mercy.
She can't breathe!

472
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,160
Hold on.

473
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,520
First, change how you address me.

474
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:52,400
Don't call me grandpa. Uncle is fine.
Grandpa hits a sore spot.

475
00:30:52,480 --> 00:30:54,880
You know why her mouth is taped up?

476
00:30:54,960 --> 00:30:56,640
This old lady's got a sharp tongue.

477
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:58,880
Alright, Uncle! Take it off first.

478
00:30:58,960 --> 00:31:00,440
I'm sorry.

479
00:31:01,040 --> 00:31:02,280
Sorry.

480
00:31:04,920 --> 00:31:05,760
You evil!

481
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:12,960
Just you wait! I'm calling my kid! Kluay!

482
00:31:13,040 --> 00:31:15,280
Kluay!

483
00:31:16,320 --> 00:31:18,640
What Kluay?

484
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:20,040
How many times have I told you?

485
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:21,760
It's Koh!

486
00:31:21,840 --> 00:31:23,880
Earlier, during the recording,
it took forever

487
00:31:23,960 --> 00:31:25,440
to get the name right!

488
00:31:25,520 --> 00:31:28,080
Whatever his name is! I'm calling my kid!

489
00:31:28,160 --> 00:31:29,480
I'm calling my kid!

490
00:31:30,840 --> 00:31:32,400
Bring it, quick!

491
00:31:32,480 --> 00:31:35,080
I told you already! I warned you!

492
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:49,800
Do you think they're planning
to keep all the money for themselves?

493
00:31:51,600 --> 00:31:53,000
Definitely.

494
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:55,880
We need to gain the upper hand
as fast as possible.

495
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:02,480
That kid,

496
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:06,000
she's definitely planning something.

497
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:09,200
Once we get all the money,

498
00:32:09,280 --> 00:32:11,920
we'll ditch them. Those brats.

499
00:32:24,040 --> 00:32:25,600
We're screwed!

500
00:32:25,680 --> 00:32:27,640
- What is it, Angpao?
- What?

501
00:32:27,720 --> 00:32:29,760
I got suspicious about Koh's mom.

502
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:32,560
So, I checked his Facebook.

503
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:36,280
Found nothing. Then I remembered
the nursing home has a Facebook page.

504
00:32:36,360 --> 00:32:37,440
When I dug through it,

505
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:40,520
I found a recent photo
from the day Koh visited his mom.

506
00:32:41,240 --> 00:32:42,440
Let me see.

507
00:32:51,000 --> 00:32:53,440
Auntie! Wake up!

508
00:32:55,600 --> 00:32:57,360
Geez! What the heck?

509
00:32:57,440 --> 00:33:00,840
Hey, answer me. Whose mom are you?

510
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:03,840
Mom? What mom?

511
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:05,120
I'm Koh's mom.

512
00:33:05,200 --> 00:33:06,240
Yeah, that's her.

513
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:08,600
No. Not this.

514
00:33:08,680 --> 00:33:10,440
What's your kid's name?

515
00:33:10,520 --> 00:33:13,680
I told you. He's Koh.

516
00:33:13,760 --> 00:33:15,520
Wait, no.

517
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:19,000
My kid's name is Khai!

518
00:33:19,080 --> 00:33:20,520
Khai! Yeah!

519
00:33:21,640 --> 00:33:23,160
Which Khai is it now?

520
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,600
Whose mom did you guys grab?

521
00:33:25,680 --> 00:33:27,320
You told us to grab

522
00:33:27,400 --> 00:33:29,680
the woman wearing the pearl necklace.

523
00:33:29,760 --> 00:33:31,400
See?

524
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:34,360
Wait. Where did you get
that pearl necklace?

525
00:33:34,440 --> 00:33:36,680
No. I didn't steal it.

526
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:39,080
I didn't take anyone's stuff.
This is mine.

527
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:41,400
Now it's clear. Listen up.

528
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:43,080
This auntie

529
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:44,720
is a crook.

530
00:33:44,800 --> 00:33:47,000
This one's trouble.

531
00:33:47,880 --> 00:33:49,720
Anyway,

532
00:33:49,800 --> 00:33:51,920
whose mom did we actually grab?

533
00:33:57,760 --> 00:33:59,800
Hong, how about this?

534
00:33:59,880 --> 00:34:03,080
We return her and go get the real mom?

535
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:05,480
Too late. They're here.

536
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:08,360
What now?

537
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:09,280
What do we do?

538
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:11,159
Calm down, everyone.

539
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:12,520
Listen to my plan.

540
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:16,679
We have to play it cool
and trick Koh into giving the money back.

541
00:34:32,679 --> 00:34:34,080
You bastards!

542
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,920
He's not picking up.

543
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:57,640
He must be mad at me.

544
00:34:58,200 --> 00:34:59,200
Are you sure?

545
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:01,160
Yes, but I'll go check--

546
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,520
Noi.

547
00:35:09,520 --> 00:35:11,480
This is so good!

548
00:35:11,560 --> 00:35:14,840
- Way better than fancy food.
<i>- Koh, I'm sorry.</i>

549
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:18,760
I got carried away eating som tam
for one meal.

550
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,680
It's you guys?

551
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,280
Where's your money?

552
00:35:41,560 --> 00:35:45,040
What are your hearts made of?
Why would you go this far?

553
00:35:52,600 --> 00:35:54,000
Leave the money there.

554
00:35:54,080 --> 00:35:55,920
Then take your mom.

555
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:57,600
This isn't about the money anymore.

556
00:35:58,200 --> 00:36:01,280
After what you did to my mom,
I'm not letting you get away with this.

557
00:36:02,120 --> 00:36:04,520
Your mom's still fine for now.

558
00:36:04,600 --> 00:36:05,880
But if you don't hand over the money,

559
00:36:05,960 --> 00:36:07,320
there'll be trouble.

560
00:36:07,400 --> 00:36:09,680
How do I know that's really my mom?

561
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:13,760
- If you want this to end…
- Yeah.

562
00:36:14,560 --> 00:36:16,640
Throw the money over. Throw it!

563
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:19,880
No. Unless I see my mom's face,

564
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:21,360
you're not getting the money.

565
00:36:21,960 --> 00:36:24,440
Throw it, or I shoot.

566
00:36:26,280 --> 00:36:27,800
Throw it!

567
00:36:32,760 --> 00:36:34,760
Chen, you ready?

568
00:36:34,840 --> 00:36:35,880
Ready.

569
00:36:36,640 --> 00:36:37,920
I said throw it!

570
00:36:38,560 --> 00:36:39,640
Throw it!

571
00:36:46,600 --> 00:36:48,400
You won't let us see Mom's face.

572
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:50,720
Then we all die together!

573
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,040
- Oh no!
- Whoa, a bomb!

574
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:01,440
- Run!
- Hey!

575
00:37:03,840 --> 00:37:05,280
Mom, it's Koh.

576
00:37:07,120 --> 00:37:08,640
Stay still. It's me.

577
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:10,320
- Mom, I'll untie you.
- Ris!

578
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:13,640
No way! Give it!

579
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:15,640
Ris!

580
00:37:17,040 --> 00:37:18,400
Shoot them, Yak! Shoot!

581
00:37:18,480 --> 00:37:20,800
- Wait!
- That's my friend! Don't shoot!

582
00:37:20,880 --> 00:37:22,040
Don't!

583
00:37:22,120 --> 00:37:23,440
Let go! Give it here!

584
00:37:23,520 --> 00:37:25,480
Chen, let's go! Mom, get up.

585
00:37:27,480 --> 00:37:28,720
Sorry, kid.

586
00:37:34,880 --> 00:37:36,400
- Risa.
- Let go of me!

587
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:38,040
Don't let them get away.

588
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:39,040
Ris!

589
00:37:39,120 --> 00:37:40,880
Go, follow them!

590
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:43,080
- Follow them, quick!
- Got it.

591
00:37:43,680 --> 00:37:44,840
Hey, kid!

592
00:37:44,920 --> 00:37:46,920
- Step back. I'll drive.
- Go ahead, Uncle!

593
00:38:10,160 --> 00:38:12,880
Chen, why the hell did you bring this kid?

594
00:38:12,960 --> 00:38:14,120
I didn't mean to bring her.

595
00:38:14,200 --> 00:38:16,760
She just clung to the bag like a gecko.

596
00:38:22,720 --> 00:38:24,480
Where are we going, Koh?

597
00:38:24,560 --> 00:38:26,880
We're going this way. They won't find us.

598
00:38:26,960 --> 00:38:29,320
And we can figure out
where to dump this little brat.

599
00:38:29,400 --> 00:38:32,320
Mom, did they hurt you?

600
00:38:37,240 --> 00:38:39,160
Where the hell did they go?

601
00:38:39,760 --> 00:38:40,600
Where is it?

602
00:38:40,680 --> 00:38:43,240
Hey, that G thing!

603
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:44,800
- G what?
- GPS!

604
00:38:44,880 --> 00:38:46,600
- Yeah.
- Right!

605
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:49,200
- We put a GPS on their car.
- I see, GPS.

606
00:38:50,120 --> 00:38:51,640
Open it.

607
00:38:52,960 --> 00:38:54,640
Hey, Uncle!

608
00:38:54,720 --> 00:38:56,760
Step on it! They're not far! Step on it!

609
00:38:56,840 --> 00:38:58,600
- Alright, stepping on it.
- Go, Phayak!

610
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:08,240
Chen!

611
00:39:08,320 --> 00:39:10,120
- What?
- Forget the money bag for now.

612
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:11,240
Help my mom first!

613
00:39:11,320 --> 00:39:13,640
What's wrong with her?
How'd she sleep like this?

614
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:15,040
Her fingers are locked up stiff!

615
00:39:15,120 --> 00:39:16,000
Well.

616
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:18,480
Mom, sorry I took so long.

617
00:39:23,680 --> 00:39:24,440
Mom!

618
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,640
- Mom? Whose mom is this?
- What?

619
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:34,280
Who is she, Chen?

620
00:39:34,360 --> 00:39:36,920
I don't know. I don't know.

621
00:39:45,560 --> 00:39:46,600
Unlock it, now.

622
00:39:52,960 --> 00:39:54,400
You wanna get stabbed?

623
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:56,080
I said unlock it.

624
00:39:57,080 --> 00:39:58,240
Hurry up.

625
00:39:58,960 --> 00:39:59,960
Where's my mom?

626
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:03,400
Well, they meant

627
00:40:03,480 --> 00:40:05,480
to grab your mom.

628
00:40:05,560 --> 00:40:07,280
But they got the wrong person.

629
00:40:08,400 --> 00:40:11,120
She's probably fine wherever she is.

630
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:14,480
As for this auntie,
I have no clue whose mom she is.

631
00:40:15,600 --> 00:40:16,520
What the hell is this?

632
00:40:18,600 --> 00:40:19,960
Gotcha.

633
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,720
Hey, don't move! Open the door now!

634
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:28,880
Get down!

635
00:40:30,160 --> 00:40:32,560
Come on.

636
00:40:32,640 --> 00:40:35,200
Easy, slowly. Come here.

637
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:37,200
Yeah, nice and slow.

638
00:40:37,280 --> 00:40:39,120
Good.

639
00:40:43,480 --> 00:40:45,720
Nice gun you've got there.
I'll take that, okay?

640
00:40:52,800 --> 00:40:53,680
What are you playing at?

641
00:40:55,840 --> 00:40:58,200
Hey, you guys grabbed the wrong person.

642
00:40:58,280 --> 00:41:00,440
You took this troublemaker auntie instead.

643
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,480
You're such a mess!

644
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:03,440
Hey.

645
00:41:03,520 --> 00:41:06,440
If you hadn't snatched my money,
none of this would've happened.

646
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,840
I didn't take your money.

647
00:41:09,920 --> 00:41:11,880
I took these kids' money.

648
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:18,320
Risa, hand the money over to me.

649
00:41:19,120 --> 00:41:22,240
If I give it to you, you'll take it all.

650
00:41:22,320 --> 00:41:24,880
You brat! I said,
hand it over, so hand it over!

651
00:41:25,680 --> 00:41:28,000
If you don't want to die,
give me the money.

652
00:41:28,600 --> 00:41:29,680
Now!

653
00:41:31,280 --> 00:41:32,880
You can try,

654
00:41:32,960 --> 00:41:33,840
if you think you're faster.

655
00:41:34,440 --> 00:41:35,920
Fine, fine.

656
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:40,360
Sis, didn't we agree
to split the money 50-50?

657
00:41:40,440 --> 00:41:43,080
Just figuring that out now?
There's no honor among thieves.

658
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:45,560
If you don't want to die,

659
00:41:45,640 --> 00:41:48,320
let go of the money right now.

660
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:50,000
Or I'll shoot!

661
00:41:51,200 --> 00:41:52,400
- Hey, let go!
- Back off!

662
00:41:52,480 --> 00:41:55,600
Leave the money,
and take that auntie in the car with you!

663
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:59,040
Go ahead. If you shoot my friend,
I'll shoot yours.

664
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,960
Risa, if you want everything

665
00:42:03,040 --> 00:42:04,720
to go smoothly,

666
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:07,760
leave the bag here
and get back in the car. Drive away.

667
00:42:07,840 --> 00:42:09,600
Otherwise, you'll get caught
in the crossfire.

668
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,000
Ris.

669
00:42:20,080 --> 00:42:23,160
Just give them the money.
Don't die for nothing like this.

670
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,920
- What's wrong?
- Risa, what are you doing?

671
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,760
Will you lower your guns
and talk this out?

672
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:10,320
Fine. Then nobody gets this damn money.

673
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,800
- Hey, put out the fire!
- Hurry!

674
00:43:17,880 --> 00:43:20,880
What the hell are you doing?

675
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,240
Alright.

676
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:35,760
Let's make a proper deal.

677
00:43:36,560 --> 00:43:38,720
There's ten million in that bag, right?

678
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:44,200
I'll take four million
to pay off Boss Kluay.

679
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,320
Two million is ours. You stole it from us.

680
00:43:47,400 --> 00:43:49,160
And the remaining four million,

681
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:50,480
you guys split among yourselves.

682
00:43:50,560 --> 00:43:53,000
Are you crazy? That's our money.

683
00:43:53,080 --> 00:43:55,960
Hold on. That's the money
you stole from us.

684
00:43:57,520 --> 00:44:00,280
Sorry. The total's
barely over two million.

685
00:44:00,360 --> 00:44:01,400
Hey.

686
00:44:01,480 --> 00:44:03,080
You three.

687
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:04,600
Let's split it between the two of us

688
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:06,560
and shoot these two idiots.

689
00:44:07,280 --> 00:44:10,720
Whoa, easy with the gun, kid.

690
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:21,240
Hello. Who's this?

691
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:26,080
Huh? What? I can't hear you.

692
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:28,840
Well.

693
00:44:29,360 --> 00:44:31,600
The signal's terrible, dear.

694
00:44:35,560 --> 00:44:38,240
Ah, got it. Who is this?

695
00:44:38,320 --> 00:44:41,240
Hey, it's me, Kluay, your son.

696
00:44:41,920 --> 00:44:43,400
Kluaykhai, Mom.

697
00:44:44,280 --> 00:44:45,880
- That voice sounds familiar.
- Right.

698
00:44:50,480 --> 00:44:51,560
We'll talk later.

699
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,680
It's me, Kluay, Mom. Kluaykhai, your son.

700
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,280
Oh.

701
00:44:59,800 --> 00:45:01,280
Kluaykhai, my son.

702
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:02,920
Yes.

703
00:45:03,000 --> 00:45:04,160
Damn.

704
00:45:04,800 --> 00:45:07,080
- Boss.
- Kluay.

705
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:08,920
Where are you, Mom?

706
00:45:09,520 --> 00:45:11,320
Oh, I'm with friends.

707
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:12,880
Oh, with friends.

708
00:45:13,840 --> 00:45:14,960
Which friends?

709
00:45:15,040 --> 00:45:16,440
Right here. These ones.

710
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:18,280
- Shoot!
- Get down.

711
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:21,000
Too fast. I didn't see anything!

712
00:45:21,080 --> 00:45:23,120
- Here!
- Take cover!

713
00:45:25,240 --> 00:45:26,480
Okay, never mind.

714
00:45:26,560 --> 00:45:28,560
I called to tell you
I'm coming to see you.

715
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:30,080
I'll be there in an hour.

716
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:32,360
Alright, see you then, okay?

717
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:33,640
Mwah.

718
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:38,280
Why is this such a mess?

719
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:41,200
There's no way out this time.
We're screwed!

720
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:43,080
- What do we do now?
- Did he see us?

721
00:45:43,160 --> 00:45:44,400
Hey, sis! What's going on now?

722
00:45:48,760 --> 00:45:49,920
- Don't!
- Give me the money!

723
00:45:50,000 --> 00:45:50,880
- Don't!
- Give it to me!

724
00:45:50,960 --> 00:45:51,920
- No!
- Give me the money!

725
00:45:52,000 --> 00:45:52,600
Let go!

726
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:54,480
Shoot me if you want!
I don't care if I die!

727
00:45:54,560 --> 00:45:56,080
Do you know who we grabbed?

728
00:45:56,160 --> 00:45:58,560
It's Boss Kluay's mom! The person
we have to return the money to!

729
00:46:00,760 --> 00:46:04,000
You guys, when are you taking me back?

730
00:46:04,080 --> 00:46:07,080
My son Kluay's coming to see me soon.

731
00:46:09,320 --> 00:46:11,440
Mom, I'm sorry.

732
00:46:11,520 --> 00:46:14,520
I just brought you out for a little trip.
I'll take you home soon, okay?

733
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:16,160
How about this? Are you hungry?

734
00:46:16,240 --> 00:46:18,880
I'll buy you a snack. Just this once,

735
00:46:18,960 --> 00:46:20,760
please don't tell Boss Kluay, okay?

736
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:23,360
If you buy me a snack,
I won't tell Boss Kluay.

737
00:46:23,440 --> 00:46:26,960
Mom! Thank you!

738
00:46:27,040 --> 00:46:29,360
You're so kind. Thank you!

739
00:46:29,440 --> 00:46:31,680
- Snacks!
- Do you know?

740
00:46:31,760 --> 00:46:33,920
He's transferred millions

741
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:36,800
into my bank account.

742
00:46:37,880 --> 00:46:40,280
Wait. I know this aunt.

743
00:46:41,120 --> 00:46:44,680
She loves bragging that her son
has tens of millions in his account.

744
00:46:44,760 --> 00:46:46,120
How about this?

745
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:48,760
We help each other
get the money out of her account,

746
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:49,680
then split it.

747
00:46:49,760 --> 00:46:52,080
I guarantee we'll get more
than if we keep fighting here.

748
00:46:52,160 --> 00:46:55,440
You want to die? That's Boss Kluay's mom!

749
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:57,880
Last time, we almost lost a leg

750
00:46:57,960 --> 00:46:59,240
because of Boss Kluay.

751
00:46:59,320 --> 00:47:02,800
Even better. That means
this aunt really does have money.

752
00:47:02,880 --> 00:47:04,760
When we get it, you guys

753
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:07,160
can use her money to pay her son back.

754
00:47:07,240 --> 00:47:09,200
And the rest of us get extra.

755
00:47:09,280 --> 00:47:11,240
Win-win. No need to fight.

756
00:47:11,320 --> 00:47:13,600
What if this aunt tells Boss Kluay?

757
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:17,920
She's got Alzheimer's.
She'll forget in no time.

758
00:47:18,480 --> 00:47:20,440
- Snacks.
- Right, Aunt?

759
00:47:24,120 --> 00:47:25,160
Snacks!

760
00:47:25,240 --> 00:47:26,400
Snacks!

761
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:29,800
Snacks! Okay?

762
00:47:41,400 --> 00:47:43,440
Boss Kluay said he's coming for his mom.

763
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:45,080
We've got less than an hour.

764
00:47:45,160 --> 00:47:48,640
Hacking the bank isn't easy.
One hour isn't enough.

765
00:47:48,720 --> 00:47:52,120
Let's just trick the aunt
into giving us her password.

766
00:47:52,720 --> 00:47:54,000
- It's easier.
- Hey.

767
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:57,560
It's her birthday. Just type it in.

768
00:47:57,640 --> 00:48:00,080
We already tried.
She doesn't remember anything.

769
00:48:00,160 --> 00:48:02,800
Aren't we overcomplicating this?
She probably didn't make

770
00:48:02,880 --> 00:48:04,280
a complicated password.

771
00:48:04,360 --> 00:48:06,400
Like 123456, for example.

772
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:09,520
Give it here.
How will we know if we don't try?

773
00:48:09,600 --> 00:48:10,360
Let's see.

774
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,400
ENTER YOUR PIN

775
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:12,640
Hey, Grandpa!

776
00:48:12,720 --> 00:48:14,640
Three tries max, or the app locks!

777
00:48:15,960 --> 00:48:17,480
Time's running out.

778
00:48:17,560 --> 00:48:20,040
Give up and return the aunt.

779
00:48:20,120 --> 00:48:23,240
If I drive her back,
it'll take ten minutes.

780
00:48:23,320 --> 00:48:26,520
Don't exaggerate.
I just had my friend check the GPS.

781
00:48:26,600 --> 00:48:28,280
It's at least half an hour away.

782
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:33,280
Dude, my friend's a speed demon.

783
00:48:33,360 --> 00:48:35,600
If he says it's doable,
it's doable. Right, Yak?

784
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,200
- Yes.
- Hey.

785
00:48:37,720 --> 00:48:38,840
Bro.

786
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:44,480
Normally, nobody hangs out with my mom.

787
00:48:59,880 --> 00:49:00,920
Aunt.

788
00:49:01,480 --> 00:49:04,880
You were lying? Is your kid really rich?

789
00:49:05,480 --> 00:49:08,120
I'm not lying. My kid really is rich.

790
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:11,680
Hey, just in my bank account alone,

791
00:49:11,760 --> 00:49:14,320
he's transferred tens of millions already.

792
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:15,440
Really.

793
00:49:16,320 --> 00:49:17,480
I don't believe you.

794
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:20,160
I'm serious! If you don't believe me,

795
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:23,880
check my phone.
My bank account's in there.

796
00:49:23,960 --> 00:49:25,720
Wait! Where is it?

797
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:28,320
- The phone!
- Where's my phone?

798
00:49:28,400 --> 00:49:29,440
Quick!

799
00:49:31,520 --> 00:49:33,120
Here it is, Aunt.

800
00:49:35,880 --> 00:49:38,480
Can you show me for real

801
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:40,720
that your kid's rich?

802
00:49:40,800 --> 00:49:43,600
I'll tell the other moms
you weren't lying.

803
00:49:43,680 --> 00:49:45,840
Sure. Here.

804
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:48,000
See for yourself.

805
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,320
Don't peek!

806
00:49:59,600 --> 00:50:01,200
Take a good look.

807
00:50:02,640 --> 00:50:03,600
MY ACCOUNT, AVAILABLE BALANCE

808
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:07,080
Can I get a closer look?

809
00:50:08,360 --> 00:50:09,480
No way.

810
00:50:16,400 --> 00:50:17,800
- Quick!
- Hurry up!

811
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:22,200
Aunt.

812
00:50:25,240 --> 00:50:29,760
- Snacks!
- Let's trade, Aunt.

813
00:50:31,320 --> 00:50:34,200
Okay, eat up!

814
00:50:37,480 --> 00:50:39,280
I need the QR code from everyone.

815
00:50:52,960 --> 00:50:55,160
Driving like this,
are they rushing to their mom's funeral?

816
00:50:55,720 --> 00:50:57,840
If she were dead, why would they rush?

817
00:51:02,360 --> 00:51:03,320
Hurry up!

818
00:51:19,120 --> 00:51:20,480
Kluaykhai!

819
00:51:21,280 --> 00:51:23,320
Hey, Mom.

820
00:51:23,400 --> 00:51:25,160
Come here. Give me a hug.

821
00:51:26,920 --> 00:51:28,000
Missed you.

822
00:51:29,280 --> 00:51:31,920
You're sitting here waiting for me.
Missed me?

823
00:51:32,000 --> 00:51:34,440
I missed you.

824
00:51:34,520 --> 00:51:37,400
Tell me, who did you go out with?

825
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:39,400
Who?

826
00:51:40,800 --> 00:51:43,880
I went with those people
who didn't believe you were rich.

827
00:51:49,160 --> 00:51:52,200
What's this? Who sent this?

828
00:51:52,280 --> 00:51:53,720
Let me see.

829
00:51:56,000 --> 00:51:57,400
TRANSFERRED 2,000,000 BAHT TO THE ACCOUNT

830
00:51:57,480 --> 00:51:58,520
TRANSFERRED 2,000,000 BAHT TO THE ACCOUNT

831
00:52:01,080 --> 00:52:02,800
VIDEO

832
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:08,280
<i>Thank you, Aunt.</i>

833
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:11,760
<i>We believe you now.</i>
<i>Your son really is rich.</i>

834
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:18,680
<i>Doing the transfer like this works, right?</i>
<i>No more fighting.</i>

835
00:52:18,760 --> 00:52:20,040
<i>Well, it's okay.</i>

836
00:52:20,120 --> 00:52:21,880
<i>Hey, kid.</i>

837
00:52:21,960 --> 00:52:25,560
<i>Honestly, we should get a bigger share.</i>

838
00:52:25,640 --> 00:52:27,080
<i>We have to deliver Boss Kluay's mom.</i>

839
00:52:27,760 --> 00:52:30,440
<i>You charge just for delivering her?</i>
<i>I could do it myself.</i>

840
00:52:30,520 --> 00:52:32,760
<i>No way, man.</i>

841
00:52:32,840 --> 00:52:35,280
<i>We don't trust you guys, okay?</i>

842
00:52:35,800 --> 00:52:36,640
<i>I'll drive.</i>

843
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:39,600
<i>Let's go.</i>

844
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:46,320
Something wrong, boss?

845
00:52:57,040 --> 00:53:00,120
Let's split up here.
Hopefully, we never meet again.

846
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,560
Once was more than enough.

847
00:53:03,840 --> 00:53:04,920
Mommy.

848
00:53:05,000 --> 00:53:06,640
I'll drive. You're hurt, aren't you?

849
00:53:06,720 --> 00:53:07,680
- Come on.
- Mom, let's go.

850
00:53:07,760 --> 00:53:10,400
Mom, this way, please. Let's go.

851
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:13,640
- This way, please.
- Wait.

852
00:53:20,120 --> 00:53:22,000
I don't like owing anyone.

853
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:25,160
Would've been better if you hadn't
caused the wound in the first place.

854
00:53:26,280 --> 00:53:29,440
If you don't want to cover a wound,
use it to cover your mouth.

855
00:53:30,080 --> 00:53:31,720
Hey, can I say something?

856
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:36,640
Now that you've got the money, quit.

857
00:53:36,720 --> 00:53:39,440
You're still young. Go do something else.

858
00:53:40,040 --> 00:53:41,520
This world is dangerous.

859
00:53:42,120 --> 00:53:43,960
It's nothing but hunters and prey.

860
00:53:44,040 --> 00:53:46,240
Only the strong survive.

861
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:49,920
You really love watching
wildlife documentaries, huh?

862
00:53:50,920 --> 00:53:53,640
What do you think you are? A hunter?

863
00:53:54,720 --> 00:53:56,360
Or maybe just prey

864
00:53:56,440 --> 00:53:59,560
fooling yourself
into thinking you're the hunter?

865
00:54:12,200 --> 00:54:15,400
Hey, you okay, Koh?
Did you hurt your wound?

866
00:54:19,000 --> 00:54:21,040
Haven't heard that line in a long time.

867
00:54:22,080 --> 00:54:24,400
What line? Who said that?

868
00:54:31,680 --> 00:54:34,760
The winners go to paradise.

869
00:54:35,720 --> 00:54:39,120
And the losers stay in hell.

870
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:40,040
FIVE YEARS EARLIER

871
00:54:40,120 --> 00:54:41,800
What kind of crazy logic is that?

872
00:54:43,240 --> 00:54:44,520
Aek!

873
00:54:44,600 --> 00:54:45,880
It's all true, really.

874
00:54:51,840 --> 00:54:52,720
Can I ask you something?

875
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:53,840
Sure.

876
00:54:54,400 --> 00:54:56,440
Have you ever thought
about leaving this world?

877
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:02,200
The gray world we're in,

878
00:55:02,840 --> 00:55:04,120
it's just an illusion.

879
00:55:05,320 --> 00:55:07,720
No one ever truly wins in it.

880
00:55:13,160 --> 00:55:14,440
What mood are you in, Aek?

881
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:17,680
Some gray-world philosophy, huh?

882
00:55:22,720 --> 00:55:24,200
You're just prey

883
00:55:25,360 --> 00:55:27,120
fooling yourself
into thinking you're the hunter.

884
00:55:29,680 --> 00:55:31,200
I used to get carried away too,

885
00:55:31,280 --> 00:55:33,400
thinking I was the big fish

886
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:36,280
swallowing smaller fish.

887
00:55:40,200 --> 00:55:41,520
But be careful.

888
00:55:42,680 --> 00:55:44,640
Sometimes the prey you swallow

889
00:55:44,720 --> 00:55:46,840
has a hook hidden inside.

890
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:49,400
Remember that.

891
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:55,960
Yes, Aek.

892
00:56:13,240 --> 00:56:15,560
The world isn't just black and white.

893
00:56:15,640 --> 00:56:17,200
Alright, let's test it.

894
00:56:17,280 --> 00:56:19,200
<i>If she finds the bag</i>

895
00:56:19,280 --> 00:56:21,720
<i>and returns it to the station, she's good.</i>

896
00:56:22,360 --> 00:56:25,280
<i>But if she steals the money inside,</i>
<i>she's bad.</i>

897
00:56:25,360 --> 00:56:26,520
Nothing left to ask, right?

898
00:56:26,600 --> 00:56:28,440
<i>Welcome, everyone.</i>

899
00:56:28,520 --> 00:56:31,640
<i>From now on, call me Admin.</i>

900
00:56:31,720 --> 00:56:34,000
<i>Boss Kluay, the one you all tricked</i>

901
00:56:34,080 --> 00:56:36,160
<i>into taking the money</i>

902
00:56:36,240 --> 00:56:38,920
<i>is hunting all of you down.</i>

903
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:41,760
Damn it! They've taken all the money!

904
00:56:41,840 --> 00:56:43,080
It's real!

905
00:56:43,160 --> 00:56:44,320
I'm sorry.

906
00:56:44,400 --> 00:56:46,560
Don't think you can mess with me
and get away with it.

907
00:56:46,640 --> 00:56:50,040
Hope you enjoy the new menu
I've prepared for you.

908
00:56:50,120 --> 00:56:52,040
What's in there?

909
00:57:41,760 --> 00:57:44,000
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
